author: Zachary R. Dowdy
title: Bellport woman crashes into Brookhaven woods
text:
Brookhaven firefighters respond to a crash on the eastbound Sunrise Highway between exits 57-56 in Brookhaven after a vehicle hit a tree and overturned around 11:35 a.m. on Wednesday, Feb. 22, 2017. Three people suffered minor injuries. (Credit: James Carbone) 

Suffolk police said a motorist lost control of her car along Sunrise Highway in Brookhaven Wednesday morning and crashed into a wooded area, overturning the vehicle and causing minor injuries to herself and two passengers. 
A Fifth Precinct officer saw Michelle Turner, 21, of Bellport, driving a Toyota Avalon along the highway near Station Road at about 11:35 a.m. when the crash occurred,...
